{
  "stem": "10829.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "You were a Jew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "You went to schul.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "You practiced Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "There was no reason not to because everything else was closed on Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And there was no reason for you not to be kosher because everything else was kosher.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "There was no reason for you not to date a Jewish girl, because everybody else was down there, and you usually didn't because you had a [YIDDISH] And if you had some money, you married your cousin, and your always kept the money in there.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Like with my family, cousins married cousins.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "The Szames married the Katzs, and it's been going on for generations.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we used to have-- most that I know of is we'd sit with dad or my [INAUDIBLE] or mom, and they used to tell you about zaides and all this.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "My name-- I'm named after my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And all going back three generations that I know of, my dad was named after his grandfather, and his grandfather is named after his grandfather.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And all of them were killed, not natural death, but they were killed by the Cossacks or the Bolsheviks and so forth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "My zaide, Itzig, was stabbed on a horse by-- by the Cossacks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "So this has been going on for-- that was no-- no novelty for being killed by the goyim, by the gentiles.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, before-- before we get this, what I remember of the beginning of the war is-- and like I said-- we were-- we were in Trochenbrod, and this is in the early '40s, or late-- they started laying cement in part of our street.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Came out where they were going to-- where they were going to pave our street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In those days, they used cement.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
